
**Default restart policy of pod is Always.

**nodeName=<nodename> nodename to be defined if particular node a pod to be scheduled.

**scheduler is responsible for scheduling a pod to node. If no scheduler running,the pod will be in pending state.

**scheduler manifest file is available in the /etc/kubernetes/manifests folder.

**Node Selector used to achieve single label not for complex conditions like place in size large or medium not in small nodes

**Taints(Nodes) and Tolerations(pods) set restrictions on which pods to be scheduled in the nodes
	* NoSchedule
	* PreferNoSchedule
	* NoExectute

